Usage: hcl [-hnbvdum] [file]

If a file is specified it will be compiled to a .js file
 otherwise the REPL will be opened.

Options:
-h, --help            Display this help message
-n, --run-with-node   Immediately execute the program using Node.js
-b, --browser         Optimize the code for use in a web browser
                       it is recommended for reliability reasons that this
                       always be used for applications meant to run in a
                       browser.
-v, --version         Display the version number
-d, --debug           Run the REPL in debug mode to see the
                       intermediate compiled JavaScript source.
-u, --underscore      Include underscore.js
-m, --minify          Minify output using uglify.js
